# install_problem_grader(~~&std_problem_grader);

ANS( str_cmp( $ml->ra_correct_ans ) );

@correct = @{$ml->ra_correct_ans()};
$answerstring = join(", ", @correct);
Context()->texStrings;

BEGIN_SOLUTION
${PAR}SOLUTION:$PAR
1. Since \(\displaystyle \lim_{x\to -1} h(x)=0\) and \(h(-1)=0\) we have that \(h(x)\) is continuous at \(x=-1\). 
$BR
$BR
2. Since \(\displaystyle \lim_{x\to 1^-} h(x)=0\) but \(\displaystyle \lim_{x\to 1^+} h(x)=1\) we have that \(\displaystyle \lim_{x\to 1} h(x)\) does not exist. Thus, \(h(x)\) is discontinuous at \(x=1\). 
$BR
$BR
Thus, the correct answers are $answerstring.
END_SOLUTION

